      "description": "This FD3S stands as a definitive example of Japanese engineering, featuring a meticulously maintained 13B-REW rotary engine with excellent compression and zero housing fatigue. The complex sequential twin-turbocharger array operates with factory precision, providing a seamless transition and consistent boost pressure across the powerband. The chassis retains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution, complemented by a rigid double-wishbone suspension and a factory-spec Torsen limited-slip differential. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed manual transmission with zero synchro wear. This vehicle has been preserved in a climate-controlled environment, ensuring all vacuum lines, cooling system components, and subframe bushings remain in peak operational condition.",
